  "rationale": "WoodWave has no logo-wall or feature-grid vocabulary, so the SaaS pattern is remapped onto editorial vocabulary. The hero is the single inverse bookend and the only accent carrier: a sanctioned display-title-over-media overlap on the staircase plate. The gallery-mosaic (collage, since bento is not drawable) carries the 'one source of truth' message as marginal caption over staggered, bleeding plates behind a heavy ghost word. The three value_props render as ONE 3-module feature-run in a cards run on cream (open, unboxed \u2014 respecting no-cards-on-cream). Social proof maps to an editorial stat+quote split on a dark panel rather than a logo wall (flagged: brand lacks a logo-wall, so the '10,000+ teams' stat + pulled quote substitute). The conversion stack closes centered per the bookend allowance, using arrow/slash links instead of buttons. Every non-hero section stays primary/panel with no accent to honor single-accent and the flat two-field system."
